# Week 1 - Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

## Objective
Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on the given dataset and understand different types of attributes.

## Tasks Performed
- Loaded the dataset into Python.
- Identified different types of attributes:
  - Numerical Attributes
  - Nominal Attributes
  - Binary Attributes
- Studied the characteristics of each attribute type.
- Measured dissimilarity between nominal attributes.
- Measured dissimilarity between numerical attributes.
- Observed and interpreted the results.

## Tools Used
- Python
- Google Colab / Jupyter Notebook
- Pandas
- NumPy

## Outcome
Successfully identified attribute types and calculated dissimilarity measures for nominal and numerical data as part of the EDA process.
